%C2%A0%26quot%3Bleaking%26quot%3B%20helium.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20findings%20could%20upend%20what%20we%20knew%20about%20our%20planet's%20core%2C%20which%20was%20thought%20to%20be%20sealed%20away.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearths-mysterious-core-is-a-lot-weirder-than-you-think-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEarth's%20mysterious%20core%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%2C%20once%20again%2C%20baffling%20scientists%20with%20its%20strange%20behavior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20study%20of%2062-million-year-old%20lava%20flows%20on%20Baffin%20Island%20in%20the%20Arctic%20Archipelago%20has%20found%20unusually%20high%20levels%20of%20helium-3%20(%C2%B3He)%2C%20a%20rare%20isotope%20that%20is%20associated%20with%20the%20insides%20of%20our%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20suggests%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearth-core-encased-by-ancient-ocean-mountains-taller-everest-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEarth's%20core%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20be%20leaking%20the%20rare%20helium%2C%20upheaving%20the%20belief%20that%20the%20giant%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearth-inner-core-ball-butter-gooier-than-hard-metal-study-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eball%20of%20molten%20iron%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20center%20of%20our%20planet%20is%20sealed%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20find%20this%20exciting%20because%20it%20suggests%20that%20the%20deep%20Earth%20is%20more%20dynamic%20than%20we%20realized%2C%26quot%3B%20Forrest%20Horton%2C%20a%20geochemist%20at%20Woods%20Hole%20Oceanographic%20Institution%20and%20lead%20author%20on%20the%20study%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vice.com%2Fen%2Farticle%2F93kgwd%2Fearths-core-appears-to-be-leaking-in-the-arctic-and-scientists-dont-know-why%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVice's%20Motherboard.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20clue%20into%20the%20Earth's%20insides%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20%C2%B3He%20is%20found%20trapped%20in%20rock%2C%20scientists%20tend%20to%20think%20it%20comes%20from%20material%20that%20was%20bombarded%20by%20the%20sun%20at%20the%20very%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmagma-ocean-inside-earth-kickstarted-magnetic-field-first-2020-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeginning%20of%20our%20planet's%20history.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20because%20Earth%20itself%20doesn't%20produce%20much%20%C2%B3He%2C%20and%20any%20%C2%B3He%20that%20escapes%20from%20Earth%20floats%20straight%20into%20space.%20Additionally%2C%20%C2%B3He%20that%20comes%20from%20solar%20radiation%20today%20bounces%20back%20to%20space%20thanks%20to%20our%20planet's%20magnetic%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20follows%20that%20high%20levels%20of%20%C2%B3He%20found%20in%20rock%20today%20would%20have%20come%20from%20the%20birth%20of%20our%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeeing%20%C2%B3He%20in%20rocks%20is%20not%20that%20uncommon%20%E2%80%94%20its%20level%20is%20measured%20as%20a%20proportion%20of%20%C2%B3He%20compared%20to%20another%20helium%20isotope%20found%20in%20rock%2C%20%E2%81%B4He.%20Scientists%20have%20traced%20most%20of%20the%20%C2%B3He-rich%20rocks%20back%20to%20the%20Earth's%20mantle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20puzzled%20scientists%20in%20this%20latest%20study%20is%20just%20how%20much%20%C2%B3He%20was%20in%20the%20Baffin%20Islands%20lava%20olivine%20rocks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224020%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Earth's%20core%20illustration%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F60c37dc56d855e00181578c6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222680%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20illustration%20of%20Earth's%20core.%3Cp%3EiStock%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%20Plus%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20%C2%B3He%2F%E2%81%B4He%20ratio%20found%20in%20the%20Baffin%20Islands%20should%20not%20be%20possible%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Earth's%20mantle%20isn't%20static.%20It's%20constantly%20spewing%20lava%20to%20the%20surface%2C%20and%20gobbling%20up%20pieces%20of%20the%20Earth's%20crust.%20With%20all%20that%20churning%2C%20some%20of%20the%20isotope%20originally%20preserved%20inside%20the%20planet%20has%20escaped%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20scientists%20say%20there's%20a%20limit%20to%20how%20much%20%C2%B3He%20can%20be%20found%20in%20a%20rock%20that%20comes%20from%20the%20mantle.%20Anything%20above%20that%20limit%20likely%20means%20the%20helium%20originates%20from%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20was%20surprising%20was%20that%20we%20measured%20%C2%B3He%2F%E2%81%B4He%20ratios%20that%20extend%20to%20much%20higher%20values%20than%20previously%20thought%2C%26quot%3B%20Horton%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20logical%20assumption%20then%2C%20is%20an%20even%20more%20challenging%20one%3A%20the%20rock%20comes%20from%20deeper%20within%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20the%20core.%20That%2C%20in%20itself%2C%20could%20rewrite%20what%20we%20know%20about%20our%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTraditionally%2C%20the%20core%20and%20outer%20layers%20of%20our%20planet%20(mantle%20and%20crust)%20were%20presumed%20to%20be%20geochemically%20isolated%20(i.e.%2C%20material%20does%20not%20transfer%20back%20and%20forth)%2C%26quot%3B%20Horton%20told%20Vice%20in%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20finding%2C%20Horton%20told%20Vice%2C%20%26quot%3Blends%20credence%20to%20the%20idea%20that%20material%2C%20or%20at%20least%20helium%2C%20leaks%20out%20of%20the%20core.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20find%20this%20exciting%20because%20it%20suggests%20that%20the%20deep%20Earth%20is%20more%20dynamic%20than%20we%20realized%3A%20elements%20move%20between%20the%20metallic%20and%20rocky%20parts%20of%20our%20planet%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20per%20Vice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20important%20question%20is%2C%20assuming%20helium%20is%20leaking%20out%20of%20the%20core%2C%20whether%20any%20other%20elements%20also%20escape%20from%20the%20core%3F%20And%20when%20did%20these%20elements%20migrate%20into%20the%20rocky%20part%20of%20the%20planet%3F%26quot%3B%C2%A0he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20were%20published%20in%20the%20peer-reviewed%20journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Dd56a245effaf86f022b0929c184dd56a7e51f64b1333bdb981790050e0748379%26postID%3D653255393f64add278f75b4f%26postSlug%3Drare-element-arctic-lava-suggest-earth-core-may-leaking-2023-10%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41586-023-06590-8.epdf%253Fsharing_token%253D6Rlg6hrGdhFv3FMWvjr5cdRgN0jAjWel9jnR3ZoTv0PKmXMX8n7E_pqStH5omCW26qpSsyne8kcCIqZL3QnJhpZiYD7KGU2QzEL5murPLAqOoKxB7Fjcrw1ystvLzgxqEiRvJjFSDQY97Q3TazPjrDGZTKNRt_S-O76K_q0l9i2oiUKV4G7SfICEdtxI5BL3WYxUSHHq2hIhXrBd4A09GA%25253D%25253D%2526tracking_referrer%253Dwww.vice.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENature%20on%20August%2030.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frare-element-arctic-lava-suggest-earth-core-may-leaking-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697807861000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65326a3696f7540cd0615402%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frare-element-arctic-lava-suggest-earth-core-may-leaking-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20study%20suggests%20the%20Earth's%20core%20may%20be%20leaking%20helium%2C%20upheaving%20the%20belief%20that%20the%20giant%20ball%20of%20molten%20iron%20at%20the%20center%20of%20our%20planet%20is%20sealed%20away.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mguenot%40businessinsider.com%20(Marianne%20Guenot)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frare-element-arctic-lava-suggest-earth-core-may-leaking-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Over%201300%20Writers%2C%20Publishers%20Decry%20Can