en%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20of%20Frankfurt%20Book%20Fair%2C%20which%20funds%20Litprom%2C%20also%20said%20it%20stands%20in%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCyV_bnoouAw%2F%5C%22%3Ecomplete%20solidarity%20on%20the%20side%20of%20Israel%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20they%20wanted%20to%20make%20Jewish%20and%20Israeli%20voices%20%E2%80%9Cespecially%20visible%20at%20the%20fair%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20also%20condemned%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Ffreedom_theatre%2Fstatus%2F1712440518880153934%2Fphoto%2F1%5C%22%3Ecancellation%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20play%20of%20Hassan%20Abdulrazzak%20%E2%80%98And%20Here%20I%20Am%E2%80%99%20by%20the%20mayor%20of%20%3Cspan%3EChoisy-le-Roi%2C%20a%20commune%20in%20France.%20Abdulrazzak%E2%80%99s%20play%20is%20around%20the%20coming-of-age%20story%20of%20actor-director%20Ahmed%20Tobasi%2C%20born%20in%20Jenin%20during%20the%20first%20intifada%20of%20Palestine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESimilarly%2C%20the%20launch%20of%20%3Cem%3EA%20Day%20in%20the%20Life%20of%20Abed%20Salama%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0Nathan%20Thrall%E2%80%99s%20book%2C%20was%20cancelled%20due%20to%20%E2%80%9Csecurity%20concerns%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20of%20support%20was%20signed%20by%2C%20among%20others%2C%20Nobel%20Prize%20laureates%20Abdulrazak%20Gurnah%2C%20Annie%20Ernaux%2C%20and%20Olga%20Tokarczuk%3B%20Booker%20Prize%20winners%20Anne%20Enright%2C%20Richard%20Flanagan%2C%20and%20Ian%20McEwan%3B%202021%20winner%20of%20the%20Litprom%20prize%20Pilar%20Quintana%20and%202015%20winner%20Madeleine%20Thien%3B%20dozens%20of%20publishers%20and%20literary%20agents%3B%20as%20well%20as%20many%20concerned%20writers%20from%20around%20the%20globe.%20There%20are%20now%20more%20than%201%2C300%20signatories%2C%20ArabLit%20said%20on%20its%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBelow%20is%20the%20letter%20of%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20shocking%20and%20tragic%20events%20that%20began%20on%20October%207th%20and%20are%20ongoing%20today%20have%20had%20repercussions%20all%20over%20the%20globe%2C%20including%20within%20the%20publishing%20world.%20Award-winning%20Palestinian%20author%20Adania%20Shibli%2C%20who%20was%20a%20finalist%20for%20the%202020%20National%20Book%20Award%20for%20her%20book%C2%A0%3Ci%3EMinor%20Detail%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0(New%20Directions%2FFitzcarraldo%2C%20translated%20by%20Elisabeth%20Jaquette)%2C%20was%20to%20receive%20Germany%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.litprom.de%2Fen%2Fbest-books%2Fliberaturpreis%2Fthe-winner-2023%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520LiBeraturpreis%25202023%26amp%3Btext%3DPalestinian%2520author%2520Adania%2520Shibli%2520receives%2COrth%252C%2520published%2520by%2520Berenberg%2520Verlag.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E2023%20LiBeraturpreis%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20the%20same%20book%2C%20published%20in%20German%20as%C2%A0%3Ci%3EEine%20Nebensache%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0(Berenberg%20Verlag%2C%20translated%20by%20G%C3%BCnther%20Orth)%20at%20the%202023%20Frankfurt%20Book%20Fair%2C%20which%20begins%20next%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20October%2013%2C%20the%20organizers%20of%20the%20prize%2C%20Litprom%2C%20which%20is%20funded%20in%20part%20by%20the%20German%20government%20and%20the%20Frankfurt%20Book%20Fair%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.litprom.de%2Fen%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereleased%20a%20statement%20saying%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0Shibli%20would%20no%20longer%20receive%20the%20prize%20during%20the%20book%20fair.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20a%20public%20discussion%20with%20Adania%20Shibli%20and%20her%20translator%20G%C3%BCnther%20Orth%20at%20the%20book%20fair%20has%20also%20been%20canceled.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20originally%20said%20that%20this%20decision%20had%20been%20made%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20author%2C%20which%20was%20then%20relayed%2C%20without%20verification%2C%20by%20an%20article%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F10%2F13%2Fbooks%2Ffrankfurt-book-fair-cancels-award-adania-shibli.html%3Funlocked_article_code%3Dod51UV2wwU5LpwBzcCN5WjlbZ9MVwjVX7RjEuujfuCZGcwCdT522_QHNlGtz6lIds9cZyKEJ-cp5J_G3htLwXhM_pZ4LYTrq4AKa20DACp3JmqXwnTpFYs3lhCk8A58Wd8p0qrTBZzCUuT0bs1BcJl41dpPiimmqXUEOcC4aX8PzEdMDG_hnNUD0Y7zAYSmgeeax2JIu5ZSMTNYiHKrV7c2SFBTnukhHA1Y0b1epsIMRaMculAP-U01ZI_Jz0fgZugTdC2LeZ4Ia06tJISkvkFPsZjarGnlanOL4_ClwlkR5EQGmw5qcke-qOqNU3FofiYqdiklOQZ8lgYT2bkdmCPbxJeD58FXzQjXy0nMMWpW4rRzGt4ST%26smid%3Durl-share%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(now%20corrected).%20This%20is%20untrue%3B%C2%A0Adania%20Shibli%20has%20said%20the%20decision%20was%20not%20made%20with%20her%2C%C2%A0she%20was%20presented%20with%20the%20decision.%20If%20the%20ceremony%20were%20held%2C%20she%20said%2C%20she%20would%20have%20taken%20the%20opportunity%20to%20reflect%20on%20the%20role%20of%20literature%20in%20these%20cruel%20and%20painful%20times.%20(Litprom%20and%20The%20Times%20have%20since%20made%20corrections.)%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShibli%E2%80%99s%20US%20publisher%2C%20Barbara%20Epler%20of%20New%20Directions%2C%20wrote%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20editor%20of%C2%A0%3Ci%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20which%20we%20excerpt%20here%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EWith%20the%20unbelievable%20heartbreak%20that%20is%20now%20being%20suffered%20on%20all%20sides%2C%20it%20serves%20no%20one%20to%20put%20forward%20falsehoods%2C%20especially%20about%20the%20author%20of%20a%20novel%20about%20the%20Nakba%20that%20is%20so%20historically%20true.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3ETo%20cancel%20the%20ceremony%20and%20so%20try%20to%20silence%20the%20voice%20of%20Adania%20Shibli%20%E2%80%94%20%E2%80%9Cdue%20to%20the%20war%20in%20Israel%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%94%20is%20cowardly.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EBut%20to%20say%20Shibli%20agreed%20(amid%20all%20the%20suffering%20in%20Gaza)%20is%20worse.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20time%20when%20the%20fair%20has%20issued%20a%20statement%20saying%20it%20wants%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCyV_bnoouAw%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emake%20Israeli%20voices%20%E2%80%9Cespecially%20visible%20at%20the%20fair%2C%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0they%20are%20closing%20out%20the%20space%20for%20a%20Palestinian%20voice.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20Shibli%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%3Ci%3EMinor%20Detail%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0has%20been%20smeared%20as%20being%20anti-Semitic%20by%20two%20journalists%20and%20literary%20editors%2C%20other%20serious%20literary%20critics%20have%20clearly%20refuted%20this%20in%20the%20German%20press%20and%20elsewhere.%20The%20book%20makes%20reference%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.haaretz.com%2F2003-10-29%2Fty-article%2Fi-saw-fit-to-remove-her-from-the-world%2F0000017f-db62-d856-a37f-ffe2fa5b0000%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewell-documented%20events%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0related%20to%20the%20rape%20of%20a%20Bedouin%20girl%20in%201949%20by%20an%20Israeli%20army%20unit.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShibli%E2%80%99s%20UK%20publisher%2C%20Jacques%20Testard%20of%20Fitzcarraldo%20writes%2C%20%E2%80%9COne%20of%20the%20purposes%20of%20literature%20is%20to%20encourage%20understanding%20and%20dialogue%20between%20cultures.%20At%20a%20time%20of%20such%20horrific%20violence%20and%20heartbreak%2C%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20book%20fair%20has%20a%20duty%20to%20champion%20literary%20voices%20from%20Palestine%20and%20Israel.%20We%20stand%20in%20solidarity%20with%20Adania%20Shibli%20and%20her%20German%20publishers%2C%20Berenberg%20Verlag.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20spirit%2C%20those%20of%20us%20involved%20in%20writing%2C%20translation%2C%20and%20publishing%20strongly%20assert%20that%20canceling%20cultural%20events%20is%20not%20the%20way%20forward.%20We%20recall%20the%20Frankfurt%20book%20fair%20supporting%20Turkish%20publishers%2C%20and%20how%20last%20year%20Ukrainian%20president%20Zelensky%20spoke%20to%20the%20fair%20in%20a%20pre-recorded%20address.%C2%A0The%20Frankfurt%20Book%20Fair%20has%20a%20responsibility%2C%20as%20a%20major%20international%20book%20fair%2C%20to%20be%20creating%20spaces%20for%20Palestinian%20writers%20to%20share%20their%20thoughts%2C%20feelings%2C%20reflections%20on%20literature%20through%20these%20terrible%2C%20cruel%20times%2C%20not%20shutting%20them%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWe%20need%20to%20look%20for%20new%20language%20and%20new%20ideas%20in%20order%20to%20approach%20these%20bleak%20times%20in%20a%20new%20way.%20For%20this%2C%20we%20need%20writers%20%E2%80%93%20including%20Palestinian%20writers%20%E2%80%93%20more%20than%20ever.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697807736000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fover-1300-writers-publishers-decry-cancellation-of-events-featuring-palestinian-authors-artists%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20letter%20of%20support%2C%20signed%20by%20several%20Nobel%20laureates%20and%20Booker%20Prize%20winners%2C%20condemned%20the%20cancellation%20of%20events%20featuring%20Palestinian%20art%2C%20voices%2C%20and%20stories%20across%20Europe%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20Hamas%20attack%20on%20Israel.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hindustan%20Zinc%20engages%20advisory%20firm%20for%20study%20on%20its%20plans%20to%20spin%20off%20biz%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697807723000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2020-07%2F25%2Ffull%2F15956