r.com%2F6532625496f7540cd0615069%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221650%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMeta's%20Chief%20AI%20Scientist%20Yann%20LeCun%20testifies%20at%20a%20US%20Senate%20intelligence%20committee%20hearing.%3Cp%3EKevin%20Dietsch%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMeta's%20chief%20AI%20scientist%20Yann%20LeCun%20said%20that%20superintelligent%20AI%20is%20unlikely%20to%20wipe%20out%20humanity.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20told%20the%20Financial%20Times%20that%20current%20AI%20models%20are%20less%20intelligent%20than%20a%20cat.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAI%20CEOs%20signed%20a%20letter%20in%20May%20warning%20that%20superintelligent%20AI%20could%20pose%20an%20%26quot%3Bextinction%20risk.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFears%20that%20AI%20could%20wipe%20out%20the%20human%20race%20are%20%26quot%3Bpreposterous%26quot%3B%20and%20based%20more%20on%20science%20fiction%20than%20reality%2C%20Meta's%20chief%20AI%20scientist%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYann%20LeCun%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F30fa44a1-7623-499f-93b0-81e26e22f2a6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etold%20the%20Financial%20Times%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20people%20had%20been%20conditioned%20by%20science%20fiction%20films%20like%20%26quot%3BThe%20Terminator%26quot%3B%20to%20think%20that%20superintelligent%20AI%20poses%20a%20threat%20to%20humanity%2C%20when%20in%20reality%20there%20is%20no%20reason%20why%20intelligent%20machines%20would%20even%20try%20to%20compete%20with%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIntelligence%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20a%20desire%20to%20dominate.%20It's%20not%20even%20true%20for%20humans%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20it%20were%20true%20that%20the%20smartest%20humans%20wanted%20to%20dominate%20others%2C%20then%20Albert%20Einstein%20and%20other%20scientists%20would%20have%20been%20both%20rich%20and%20powerful%2C%20and%20they%20were%20neither%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rapid%20explosion%20of%20generative%20AI%20tools%20such%20as%20ChatGPT%20over%20the%20past%20year%20has%20sparked%20fears%20over%20the%20potential%20future%20risks%20of%20superintelligent%20artificial%20intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20OpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%2C%20DeepMind%20CEO%20Demis%20Hassabis%2C%20and%20Anthropic%20CEO%20Dario%20Amodei%20all%20signed%20a%20public%20statement%20warning%20that%20AI%20could%20in%20future%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-extinction-risk-openai-deepmind-anthropic-ceos-sam-altman-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epose%20an%20'extinction'%20risk%20comparable%20to%20nuclear%20war%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20fierce%20debate%20over%20how%20close%20current%20models%20are%20to%20this%20hypothesized%20%26quot%3BArtificial%20General%20Intelligence%26quot%3B%20(AGI).%20A%20study%20conducted%20by%20Microsoft%20earlier%20this%20year%20said%20that%20OpenAI's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-open-ai-balancing-task-convinced-microsoft-agi-closer-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EGPT-4%20model%20showed%20%26quot%3Bsparks%20of%20AGI%26quot%3B%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20how%20it%20approached%20reasoning%20problems%20in%20a%20human-like%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20LeCun%20told%20the%20Financial%20Times%20that%20many%20AI%20companies%20had%20been%20%26quot%3Bconsistently%20over-optimistic%26quot%3B%20over%20how%20close%20current%20generative%20models%20were%20to%20AGI%2C%20and%20that%20fears%20over%20AI%20extinction%20were%20overblown%20as%20a%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20%5Bthe%20models%5D%20just%20do%20not%20understand%20how%20the%20world%20works.%20They're%20not%20capable%20of%20planning.%20They're%20not%20capable%20of%20real%20reasoning%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20debate%20on%20existential%20risk%20is%20very%20premature%20until%20we%20have%20a%20design%20for%20a%20system%20that%20can%20even%20rival%20a%20cat%20in%20terms%20of%20learning%20capabilities%2C%20which%20we%20don't%20have%20at%20the%20moment%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeCun%20said%20that%20reaching%20human-level%20intelligence%20required%20%26quot%3Bseveral%20conceptual%20breakthroughs%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20and%20suggested%20that%20AI%20systems%20would%20likely%20pose%20no%20threat%20even%20when%20they%20hit%20that%20level%2C%20as%20they%20could%20be%20encoded%20with%20%26quot%3Bmoral%20character%26quot%3B%20that%20would%20prevent%20them%20from%20going%20rogue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Insider%2C%20made%20outside%20normal%20working%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuperintelligent-ai-will-not-destroy-humanity-meta-ai-scientist-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697803250000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65326be096908fd7cdb37b53%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuperintelligent-ai-will-not-destroy-humanity-meta-ai-scientist-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Fears%20that%20AI%20could%20wipe%20out%20the%20human%20race%20are%20%26quot%3Bpreposterous%26quot%3B%20and%20based%20more%20on%20science%20fiction%20than%20reality%2C%20Meta's%20chief%20AI%20scientist%20has%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tcarter%40insider.com%20(Tom%20Carter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuperintelligent-ai-will-not-destroy-humanity-meta-ai-scientist-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22China%20sends%20envoy%20to%20Middle%20East%20in%20sign%20of%20its%20ambition%20to%20play%20larger%20role%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697803028000%