itions%20to%20the%20top%20court%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20had%20opposed%20same-sex%20marriages.%20It%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Furban-elitist-views-centre-files-affidavit-in-sc-opposing-same-sex-marriages%5C%22%3Ehad%20argued%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20institution%20of%20marriage%20is%20%E2%80%9Cexclusively%20heterogenous%E2%80%9D%20and%20those%20seeking%20same-sex%20marriages%20represent%20%E2%80%9Curban%20elitist%20views%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20social%20acceptance%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20had%20said%20that%20same-sex%20marriage%20is%20not%20%E2%80%9Ccomparable%20with%20the%20Indian%20family%20unit%20concept%20of%20a%20husband%2C%20a%20wife%20and%20children%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20while%20delivering%20the%20judgment%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fmarriage-equality-supreme-court-decision%5C%22%3Enoted%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CQueerness%20is%20not%20urban%20or%20elite.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20not%20an%20English%20speaking%20man%20with%20a%20white%20collar%20man%20who%20can%20claim%20to%20be%20queer%20but%20equally%20a%20woman%20working%20in%20an%20agricultural%20job%20in%20a%20village%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6Queerness%20can%20be%20regardless%20of%20one%E2%80%99s%20caste%20or%20class%20or%20socio-economic%20status.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20data-testid%3D%5C%22paragraph-8%5C%22%3EPrevious%20US%20State%20Department%20reports%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Freut.rs%2F42vuoqn%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22Link%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20raised%20concerns%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20treatment%20of%20religious%20minorities%2C%20journalists%2C%20and%20dissidents%20in%20India.%20However%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fbiden-says-will-talk-human-rights-rule-law-with-modi-2023-06-22%2F%5C%22%3Ehas%20declined%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20any%20such%20discrimination%20exists%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697781910000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F18190519%2FDelhi-Pride-Parade-LGBTQ-rights-13.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fus-monitoring-indian-govts-follow-up-steps-after-sc-declines-to-legalise-same-sex-marriage%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Saying%20that%20it%20'supports%20marriage%20equality%20globally'%2C%20the%20US%20has%20encouraged%20India%20to%20work%20towards%20offering%20equal%20legal%20protection%20to%20same-sex%20couples.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fus-monitoring-indian-govts-follow-up-steps-after-sc-declines-to-legalise-same-sex-marriage%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mohammad%20Zubair%20of%20AltNews%20Hopes%20His%20Index%20on%20Censorship%20Award%20Will%20Be%20a%20%E2%80%98Flicker%20of%20Hope%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F20105552%2FMZ1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Index%20on%20Censorship%20award%20for%20Journalism%2C%202023%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FIndexCensorship%2Fstatus%2F1715097987959881940%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Ehas%20been%20won%20by%20Mohammad%20Zubair%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20one%20of%20the%20founding%20members%20of%20well-respected%20fact-checking%20organisation%20%3Cem%3EAltNews%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20Index%20said%20of%20Zubair%20that%20%E2%80%9Chis%20fight%20against%20fake%20news%20and%20disinformation%20in%20India%20has%20led%20to%20him%20facing%20attacks%2C%20slander%20and%20even%20jail%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Index%20on%20Censorship%20is%20a%20non-governmental%20group%20that%20campaigns%20for%20and%20defends%20free%20expression%20globally.%20They%20%E2%80%9Cpublish%20work%20by%20censored%20writers%20and%20artists%2C%20promote%20debate%2C%20and%20monitor%20threats%20to%20free%20speech.%E2%80%9D%20They%20added%2C%20significantly%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20all%20share%20in%20his%20%5BZubair%E2%80%99s%5D%20campaign%20for%20transparent%20and%20accurate%20news.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EZubair%20after%20winning%20the%20award%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20been%20an%20honour%20and%20a%20privilege%20to%20receive%20the%20Index%20%5Bon%20Censorship%5D%20award%2C%20especially%20at%20a%20time%20when%20fake%20news%20and%20disinformation%20has%20emerged%20as%20a%20Frankenstein%20monster%20here%20in%20India.%20I%20hope%20this%20award%20will%20serve%20as%20a%20flicker%20of%20hope%20to%20several%20other%20younger%20journalists%2C%20my%20colleagues%20at%20AltNews%20and%20the%20readers%20of%20AltNews.%20Lastly%2C%20I%20want%20to%20thank%20everyone%20who%20stood%20by%20me%20when%20I%20was%20attacked%2C%20slandered%20and%20even%20jailed%20for%20doing%20my%20job.%20Thank%20you.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhen%20Zubair%20was%20nominated%20last%20month%2C%20the%20Index%20referred%20to%20his%20arrest%20in%20June%202022%2C%20saying%20it%20is%20representative%20of%20the%20significant%20threats%20he%20has%20faced%20after%20challenging%20mis%20and%20disinformation%20propagated%20by%20influential%20members%20of%20the%20ruling%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndex%20on%20Censorship%20CEO%20Ruth%20Anderson%20had%20said%20said%20that%20the%C2%A0Freedom%20of%20Expression%20Awards%20are%20a%20%E2%80%9Cchance%20to%20recognise%20the%20astonishing%20work%20being%20done%20in%20extraordinary%20circumstances%20by%20artists%2C%20journalists%2C%20and%20campaigners%20around%20the%20world%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20awards%20they%20give%20are%20across%20four%20categories%20of%20Arts%2C%20Campaigning%2C%20Journalism%20and%20the%20Trustee%20award.%20The%20other%20two%20nominees%20on%20the%20shortlist%20were%20Bilan%20Media%2C%20which%20is%20Somalia%E2%80%99s%20first%20women-only%20media%20organisation%20and%20newsroom%2C%20and%20Afghan-French%20journalist%20and%20filmmaker%20Mortaza%20Behboudi%20who%20was%20forced%20to%20leave%20Afghanistan%20in%20his%20youth%20due%20to%20previous%20threats%20as%20a%20result%20of%20his%20reporting%2C%20and%20was%20detained%20by%20the%20Taliban%20in%20January%20in%20Kabul.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20Sophia%20Huang%20Xueqin%20received%20the%20award.%20She%20is%20a%20Chinese%20activist%20and%20journalist.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndex%20on%20Censorship%20is%20based%20in%20London%20and%20also%20brings%20out%20a%20quarterly%20magazine%20devoted%20to%20calling%20out%20censorship%20and%20standing%20for%20free%20expression.%20Poet%C2%A0Stephen%20Spender%20was%20closely%20associated%20with%20this%20venture.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697780714000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F20105552%2FMZ1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fmohammad-zubair-of-altnews-hopes-his-index-on-censorship-award-will-be-a-flicker-of-hope%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Index%20on%20Censorship%20while%20awarding%20him%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20all%20share%20in%20his%20campaign%20for%20transparent%20and%20accurate%20news.%E2%80%9D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A33%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fmohammad-zubair-of-altnews-hopes-his-index-on-censorship-award-will-be-a-flicker-of-hope%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Residents%20leave%20as%20tension%20grows%20at%20Israel-Lebanon%20border%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697779995000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F7FCE%2Fproduction%2F_131481723_fbc6c925ba7856c972a8c5854e6231587b5776e10_0_4928_32801000x666.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-67158836%22%2C%22summary%22%